g.text: The New York Archival Society (NYAS) was established in YEAR to support the work of the New York City Municipal Archives at the Department of Records and Information Services. The NYAS is governed by a Board of Directors who serve for three-year terms and may be elected for successive terms. The Board of Directors elects three officersthe President, who must be a Director, and the Secretary and Treasurer, who are not required to be Directors. The Board may establish committees and may elect a Vice Chair.The organization of the New York Archival Society in 2025 is shown below.
